        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:58PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 558 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles south of Belt, or 33 miles southeast of Great Falls, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sluice Boxes State Park and Monarch.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
